Thank you for using imgurDiscoverer.

How to run: ( fancy way )
1.) extract to a folder of you choice ( /opt/ might be a good one )
2.) give "run.sh" executable rights
3.) create a new .desktop file 
4.) in you .desktop file use the path to "run.sh" as executable
5.) in your .desktop file user the path to "imgurDiscoverer.png" as icon
6.) place the file to your ~/.local/share/applications folder
7.) give your new .desktop file executable rights
8.) double click on the .desktop file

How to run: ( fast way )
1.) extract to a folder of you choice ( /opt/ might be a good one )
2.) give "run.sh" executable rights
3.) run "run.sh"
